sentences: Lawrence Vavra (born 15 November 1977) is an American Media Entrepreneur and Private Equity Investor.

The company SFX Entertainment, now known as LiveStyle quickly raised $250 million to create the Live Nation of Electronic Dance Music, culminating in an initial public offering on October 9, 2013 on the NASDAQ, valuing the company at over $1B.  Vavra and the Gabriel Moreno sued co-founder Robert Sillerman for fraud, and breach of partnership.
The suit was subsequently settled in 2016 for an undisclosed amount.
